metadata.name: SQUARE GAMES #57
metadata.description:
Quite frankely: a lot of squares

An exploration of recursion
featuring very vibrant color combinations
Interactive

4 recursion depths
16 color palettes
4 expansion states
4 fill probabilities 
4 ghost probabilities 

Press 's' to save a high res image
Click and move mouse to explore
Press 'space' to return to original position
Press 'b' to change color of white cube
Press ‚f‘ for fullscreen
Press 'p‘ to toggle pixel perfect rendering

metadata.name: Omega Point #131
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Damn everything but the circus! #171
metadata.description:
🎪 “Damn everything but the circus! ...damn everything that is grim, dull, motionless, unrisking, inward turning, damn everything that won't get into the circle, that won't enjoy. That won't throw its heart into the tension, surprise, fear and delight of the circus, the round world, the full existence...”
― E.E. Cummings

Made with p5.js

----

Credits:
The code that checks if a point is inside an irregular path was inspired by an Amy Goodchild's tweet
https://twitter.com/amygoodchild/status/1499440104129105920

metadata.name: Yellow House #53
metadata.description:
It is very easy to forget the beauty of the places we consume because they are available to us by nature.
The things we consume all our lives we find not so special.
It’s very hard to remember how special and valuable these things really are.

With this work, I will try to give sincere admiration and respect to my favorite place on the beach!

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 'f' to save .png with resolution = 4000px x 4000px

Created using p5js ,100% p5.js code and math.

@Mutart, April, 2022.
